Rating: 3
This is the second time I've made this dish. You do NOT need to hassle with the bones. I got boneless lamb shoulder. Saved tons of time and potential loss of fingers. Recipie is just as good this way. Also altered a few things: Fried bacon and used bacon fat in addition to lamb fat. Crumbled bacon and put in stew. Floured lamb for browning. Added fresh garlic with frying onions and carrots. Used more stout than water. Used dryed thyme. Also smashed about 10 cloves which brings out a nice flavor. Made with garlic/irish cheddar mashed potatoes. Boil potatoes in chicken stock with mashing. Gives a killer flavor.

