Made this for St. Patrick's day. I agree with the one comment that separating the bones and fat can be fairly time-consuming and difficult. The end result is excellent though. Tasty and filling. I added beer in place of one of the cups of water.

Rating: 2
I thought this dish was a bit bland. I would also use stew meat --instead of cutting meat from bones. I thought this made the dish more difficult without making it better. Also too much meat --and I would use either very very small whole potatoes or else chopped potatoes, because potatoes if too big tend to get in the way of the other ingredients when dishing out for a crowd. The flavors in this dish were improved the second day -- I would not make this dish again without variation.

Rating: 3
Although the end product was good, I was highly frustrated by the process of removing the meat and fat from the bone. If you're going to do this, I suggest simply buying 2 or three pounds of lamb stew meat and 1 or 2 pounds of lamb shoulder with the bone in. Once the bones have stewed, you may easily remove the meat. Otherwise, you're apt to slice off an appendage in your efforts to get any amount of meat off the bone. I agree you should add some Stout or Ale instead of water -- otherwise the stew can be a bit bland

